  "description": [
    "British to Nationalize German Metal Industry Bad Ovenhausen Germanv Aug 21 UP The British Control Commission today took over the en tire German iron and steel industry in the British occupation zone The seizure of the industrial as sets valued at several billion dollars was described as a move toward quasinationalization of iron and ateel in the occupation area The Krupp Stinnes Vereinigte Stahlmake and other world famous steel firms in the Ruhr and Rhine land were among those over which the control commission assumed ownership Most directors of the firms were In Allied custody as suspected war criminals Many wall be tried An official statement on the move raid This step was taken in pursuance with British policy and in accord ance with Article 12 of the Berlin Protocol to establish firm control over the major German industrial potential and break down the in fluence of excessive concentrations of economic power To this end the firms of Fried rich Krupp and I G FarbenIndus trte already have been taken over and the dissolution of the com plexes found in these industries al ready is in hand The capacity of the German Steel industry in the British zone before and"
